cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with human parsing, which is a computer vision task that involves segmenting an image into semantic parts of the human body. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel self-supervised learning approach, which involves training a neural network without the need for extra supervision. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of a large dataset with detailed annotations, which could place it in the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also discusses the limitations of existing approaches, which could make it relevant to the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
